  "text": "At both Knudsen numbers numerical results provided by the the coupled scheme are in good agreement with numerical results provided by the NB scheme. The oscillations present in the NB solution especially ahead of the shock are clearly given by stochastic noise. In fact they disappear with smoothing, see [CITATION_1] . The plots show the smoothness of the matching between the different solutions, which is due to the reduced noise of the Boltzmann solver and to the matching conditions in the convective fluxes. The agreement between the NB and the coupled scheme solution persists also at the microscopic level, see Fig. 7 . We also note that the kinetic region remains correctly quite thin for small Kn ∞ . Note also the lack of stochastic noise in the 'B' regions, compared with NB.",
